#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:329
#, no-c-format
msgid "Annotating images from the viewer"
msgstr "Označevanje slik iz pregledovalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are three modes to annotating images in the viewer:"
msgstr "Za označevanje slik v pregledovalniku so na voljo trije načini:"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Locked</emphasis> - This is the default mode when starting the "
"viewer - in here no annotating or tokenizing will happen. This ensure you do "
"not accidentally annotate images when viewing them."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Zaklenjeno</emphasis> – To je privzeti način ob zagonu "
"pregledovalnika – tukaj ne bo prišlo do označevanja ali zaklepa z žetoni. "
"Tako zagotovite, da med ogledovanjem slik po nesreči ne dodate opomb."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Assign Tokens</emphasis> - This allows you to set tokens on "
"images, by simply pressing a key from A-Z on the keyboard."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Dodeljevanje žetonov</emphasis> - To vam omogoča, da nastavite "
"žetone na slike s preprostim pritiskom tipke od A do Z na tipkovnici."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Assign Tags</emphasis> - This allows you to assign macros to a "
"keyboard key. As an example, <emphasis>L</emphasis> could mean set the item "
"<emphasis>Las Vegas</emphasis> in the <emphasis>Location</emphasis> "
"category. In addition to that, it also allows you to set any tag on an image."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Dodeljevanje oznak</emphasis> – To vam omogoča, da tipki na "
"tipkovnici dodelite makre. Na primer, <emphasis>L</emphasis> bi lahko "
"pomenil nastavitev elementa <emphasis>Las Vegas</emphasis> v kategoriji "
"<emphasis>Lokacija</emphasis>. Poleg tega vam omogoča tudi nastavitev katere "
"koli oznake na sliki."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The modes are selected from the context menu as can be seen in <xref linkend="
"\"fig-ctxmenu-for-mode-selection\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Načini so izbrani iz kontekstnega menija, kot je razvidno iz <xref linkend="
"\"fig-ctxmenu-for-mode-selection\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "The two modes are described in details below."
msgstr "Ta dva načina sta podrobno opisana spodaj."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting annotation mode from the viewer"
msgstr "Izbira načina opomb v pregledovalniku"

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Tokens from the Viewer"
msgstr "Nastavitev žetonov iz pregledovalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine you want to sent a number of images to a printer to get them "
"developed on paper. To see which you want, you start the viewer on the "
"images, and tag them as <emphasis>good</emphasis>, <emphasis>bad</emphasis>, "
"or <emphasis>maybe</emphasis>, while inspecting each one."
msgstr ""
"Predstavljajte si, da želite tiskalniku poslati številne slike, da jih "
"razvijete na papir. Če želite videti, katere želite, zaženete pregledovalnik "
"na slikah in jih označite kot <emphasis>dobra</emphasis>, <emphasis>slaba</"
"emphasis> ali <emphasis>morda</emphasis>, medtem ko pregledujete vsako ."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may of course create a few new items (say <emphasis>Good</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Bad</emphasis>, <emphasis>Maybe</emphasis>) for an existing "
"category, say the category <emphasis>Album</emphasis>. However, given that "
"you likely do not need these tags once you've send the images to the "
"printer, there is an easier way, namely by simply setting tokens on the "
"images. Tokens are named from A to Z, and you set a token simply by pressing "
"its letter. In <xref linkend=\"fig-images-with-tokens\"/> you may see an "
"image where the tokens A, B and C are set."
msgstr ""
"Seveda lahko ustvarite nekaj novih elementov (recimo <emphasis>Dobro</"
"emphasis>, <emphasis>Slabo</emphasis>, <emphasis>Morda</emphasis>) za "
"obstoječo kategorijo, recimo kategorijo <emphasis>Album </emphasis>. Vendar "
"glede na to, da teh oznak verjetno ne potrebujete, ko slike pošljete v "
"tiskalnik, obstaja lažji način, in sicer tako, da na slike preprosto "
"nastavite žetone. Žetoni so poimenovani od A do Z, žeton pa nastavite "
"preprosto s pritiskom na njegovo črko. V <xref linkend=\"fig-images-with-"
"tokens\"/> boste morda videli sliko, kjer so nastavljeni žetoni A, B in C."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "An Image with Tokens"
msgstr "Slika z žetoni"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For this to work, you need to be in the <emphasis>Assign Tokens</emphasis> "
"mode. See <xref linkend=\"fig-ctxmenu-for-mode-selection\"/>"
msgstr ""
"Da bo to delovalo, morate biti v načinu <emphasis>Dodeli žetone</emphasis>. "
"Glejte <xref linkend=\"fig-ctxmenu-for-mode-selection\"/>"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once you've set tokens on your images, they will be available for regular "
"browsing in the browser, as can be seen in <xref linkend=\"fig-tokens-in-"
"browser\"/>. So when you've marked images that needs to be edited, printed, "
"or whatever, simply browse to the images, and process the set from there, e."
"g. by using <emphasis>copy images to...</emphasis> from the context menu."
msgstr ""
"Ko nastavite žetone na svoje slike, bodo na voljo za redno brskanje v "
"brskalniku, kot je razvidno v <xref linkend=\"fig-tokens-in-browser\"/>. "
"Torej, ko označite slike, ki jih je treba urediti, natisniti ali karkoli "
"drugega, preprosto pobrskajte po slikah in od tam obdelajte nabor, npr. z "
"uporabo <emphasis>kopiraj slike v...</emphasis> iz kontekstnega menija."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:387
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tokens seen in the Browser"
msgstr "Žetoni, vidni v brskalniku"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:396
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Categories (and esp tokens) may be displayed in the thumbnail viewer. When "
"Showing the categories in the thumbnail viewer, you may also add tokens to "
"images, simply by pressing the letter for the token when the image is "
"selected, this can be seen in <xref linkend=\"fig-tokens-in-thumbnail-viewer"
"\"/>"
msgstr ""
"Kategorije (in posebej žetoni) so lahko prikazane v pregledovalniku sličic. "
"Ko prikazujete kategorije v pregledovalniku sličic, lahko slikam dodate "
"žetone, tako da preprosto pritisnete črko za žeton, ko je slika izbrana, to "
"lahko vidite v <xref linkend=\"fig-tokens-in-thumbnail-viewer\"/>"

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:403
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tokens seen in the Thumbnail Viewer"
msgstr "Žetoni, vidni v pregledovalniku sličic"

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tagging images from the viewer"
msgstr "Označevanje slik iz pregledovalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tagging images can be tiresome, even in &kphotoalbum;, at least when you've "
"fallen behind and have thousands or tens of thousands of images in need of "
"proper tagging. Fortunately, it is now possible to add tags with the press "
"of a single key when viewing the images. The realization behind this way of "
"working with images is that most images are with the same few people in the "
"same few places, plus a few \"guest\" appearances from time to time - say "
"the location of your vacation, or some friends who were visiting you for a "
"week."
msgstr ""
"Označevanje slik je lahko naporno, tudi v &kphotoalbum;, vsaj če zaostajate "
"in imate na tisoče ali desettisoče slik, ki jih je treba pravilno označiti. "
"Na srečo je zdaj mogoče dodati oznake s pritiskom ene same tipke med "
"ogledovanjem slik. Spoznanje, ki stoji za tem načinom dela s slikami, je, da "
"je večina slik z istimi nekaj ljudmi na istih nekaj mestih, plus nekaj "
"\"gostujočih\" nastopov od časa do časa - recimo lokacija vašega dopusta ali "
"nekaj prijateljev, ki so bili na obisku za kak teden."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To tag your images while viewing them, you need to enter the "
"<emphasis>Assign Tags mode</emphasis> - see <xref linkend=\"fig-ctxmenu-for-"
"mode-selection\"/>. With this enabled, simply press a letter key on your "
"keyboard to either assign or use the assigned tag."
msgstr ""
"Če želite označiti svoje slike med ogledovanjem, morate vstopiti v "
"<emphasis>način za dodelitev oznak</emphasis> - glejte <xref linkend=\"fig-"
"ctxmenu-for-mode-selection\"/>. Ko je to omogočeno, preprosto pritisnite "
"tipko s črko na tipkovnici, da dodelite ali uporabite dodeljeno oznako."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <xref linkend=\"fig-assign-macro-step1\"/> below, I've just pressed "
"<keycap>s</keycap> while watching images and being in the <emphasis>Assign "
"Tags mode</emphasis>. This brought up the dialog where I can specify what "
"tag to assign to that key."
msgstr ""
"V <xref linkend=\"fig-assign-macro-step1\"/> spodaj sem pravkar pritisnil "
"<keycap>s</keycap> med gledanjem slik in v <emphasis>načinu za dodelitev "
"oznak</emphasis>. Prikaže se pogovorno okno, v katerem lahko določim, katero "
"oznako naj dodelim tej tipki."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Step 1 - assigning a macro to the key <emphasis>s</emphasis>"
msgstr "1. korak – dodelitev makra tipki <emphasis>s</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next, in the line edit I typed <emphasis>sp</emphasis> which suggest "
"\"People / Je<emphasis>sp</emphasis>er\" and \"People / <emphasis>Sp</"
"emphasis>iff\". Both matched the letters I typed. Pressing arrow down to "
"select <emphasis>Spiff</emphasis> and pressing enter, will assign the letter "
"<emphasis>s</emphasis> to adding the tag <emphasis>People / Spiff</emphasis> "
"to the image viewed. This assignment, will be saved for future sessions. To "
"re-assign s to another tag, simply press <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;"
"<keycap>s</keycap></keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"Nato sem v vrstici za urejanje vnesel <emphasis>sp</emphasis>, ki predlaga "
"\"Ljudje / Je<emphasis>sp</emphasis>er\" in \"Ljudje / <emphasis>Sp</"
"emphasis>iff\". Oba sta se ujemala s črkami, ki sem jih vtipkal. Če "
"pritisnete puščico navzdol, da izberete <emphasis>Spiff</emphasis>, in "
"pritisnete enter, dodelite črko <emphasis>s</emphasis> za dodajanje oznake "
"<emphasis>Ljudje / Spiff</emphasis> na prikazano sliko. Ta naloga bo "
"shranjena za prihodnje seje. Če želite s ponovno dodeliti drugi oznaki, "
"preprosto pritisnite <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>s</keycap></"
"keycombo>."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid "Step 2 - assigning a macro - typing <emphasis>sp</emphasis>"
msgstr "2. korak – dodelitev makra – tipkanje <emphasis>sp</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <xref linkend=\"fig-assign-macro-overview\"/> below you can see existing "
"keybindings in the right side of the dialog."
msgstr ""
"V <xref linkend=\"fig-assign-macro-overview\"/> spodaj si lahko ogledate "
"obstoječe vezave tipk na desni strani pogovornega okna."

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview of assigned key bindings"
msgstr "Pregled dodeljenih vezav tipk"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case the tag you want to assign doesn't already exist in your database, "
"then simply press the <emphasis>Add New</emphasis> button to create it. This "
"can be seen in <xref linkend=\"fig-assign-macro-add-new-value.png\"/> below"
msgstr ""
"Če oznaka, ki jo želite dodeliti, še ne obstaja v vaši bazi podatkov, "
"preprosto pritisnite gumb <emphasis>Dodaj novo</emphasis>, da jo ustvarite. "
"To si lahko ogledate v <xref linkend=\"fig-assign-macro-add-new-value.png\"/"
"> spodaj"

#. Tag: title
#: viewer.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a new tag"
msgstr "Dodajanje nove oznake"

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While tagging images from the viewer, you may want to add a tag without "
"binding it to a key. To do so simply press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>a</"
"keycap></keycombo>. This is also how you open the dialog to see the macro "
"key bindings."
msgstr ""
"Med označevanjem slik iz pregledovalnika lahko dodate oznako, ne da bi jo "
"vezali na tipko. To storite tako, da preprosto pritisnete <keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>a</keycap></keycombo>. Tako odprete tudi pogovorno okno za ogled "
"povezav makro tipk."

#. Tag: para
#: viewer.docbook:465
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Press <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>c</keycap></keycombo> to copy annotations from "
"the previous image in the viewer list."
msgstr ""
"Pritisnite <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>c</keycap></keycombo>, da kopirate opombe "
"iz prejšnje slike na seznamu pregledovalnikov."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If several images was loaded into the viewer, you can ask it to run them "
#~ "as a slide show, which means that &kphotoalbum; loads a new image every "
#~ "few second. How often it loads a new image is configure by pressing the "
#~ "control key and respective plus (for go faster) or minus (go slower). "
#~ "Starting and stopping the slide show is done simply by pressing "
#~ "<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Če je bilo v pregledovalnik naloženih več slik, ga lahko prosite, da jih "
#~ "zažene kot predstavitev, kar pomeni, da &kphotoalbum; naloži novo sliko "
#~ "vsakih nekaj sekund. Kako pogosto naloži novo sliko, se konfigurira s "
#~ "pritiskom na tipko za upravljanje in ustreznim plusom (za hitrejšo "
#~ "vožnjo) ali minusom (počasneje). Predstavitev zaženete in zaustavite "
#~ "preprosto s pritiskom <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo>."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "A very useful feature of the &kphotoalbum; viewer is it ability to go "
#~ "into full screen mode. In this mode, the viewer is using the complete "
#~ "screen space, simply press the return key to make it go into and out of "
#~ "full screen mode."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Zelo uporabna funkcija &kphotoalbum; pregledovalnika je možnost preklopa "
#~ "v celozaslonski način. V tem načinu gledalec uporablja celoten prostor na "
#~ "zaslonu, preprosto pritisnite tipko za vrnitev, da preide v celozaslonski "
#~ "način in iz njega."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Notice, for technical the only zooming operation that works when watching "
#~ "videos are zoom in and out (the plus and minus key)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Upoštevajte, da je tehnično edina operacija povečave, ki deluje pri "
#~ "gledanju videoposnetkov, povečava in pomanjšava (tipki plus in minus)."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Choosing the rotate operations from the context menu, you may rotate the "
#~ "image (Does not work for videos). You can annotate the current image, "
#~ "simply by choosing <guimenuitem>Annotate</guimenuitem> in the context "
#~ "menu."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Če v kontekstnem meniju izberete operacijo vrtenja, lahko zasukate sliko "
#~ "(ne deluje za videoposnetke). Trenutno sliko lahko označite tako, da "
#~ "preprosto izberete <guimenuitem>Pripomba</guimenuitem> v priročnem meniju."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Traditionally the main way for tagging images has been though <link "
#~ "linkend=\"chp-typingIn\">the annotation dialog</link>. Over the years a "
#~ "few different attempts have been made at integrating tagging into the "
#~ "viewer, first attempt was by assigning tokens in the viewer, a later "
#~ "attempt was by making it possible to tag directly by typing part of a "
#~ "category item. In addition category items could be assigned to function "
#~ "keys on the keyboard. The code for all of this have now been modernized "
#~ "to make the work flow much more intuitive and discover-able."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Tradicionalno je bil glavni način za označevanje slik skozi <link linkend="
#~ "\"chp-typingIn\">pogovorno okno za opombe</link>. V preteklih letih je "
#~ "bilo narejenih nekaj različnih poskusov integracije označevanja v "
#~ "pregledovalnik, prvi poskus je bil z dodeljevanjem žetonov v "
#~ "pregledovalniku, kasnejši poskus je bil z omogočanjem neposrednega "
#~ "označevanja s tipkanjem dela postavke kategorije. Poleg tega bi lahko "
#~ "elemente kategorij dodelili funkcijskim tipkam na tipkovnici. Koda za vse "
#~ "to je zdaj posodobljena, tako da je potek dela veliko bolj intuitiven in "
#~ "ga je mogoče odkriti."
